During this AB, Holm hit a ball down the 1B line just foul. Mueller had dashed for 2B and ran into Ford.  The two began a fist fight, and rolled around on the ground for a few seconds.  They had to be separated by the combined efforts of both teams.  Sand accused Mueller of throwing dirt in his eyes.  Neither was ejected.
Critz made a great running catch.
Account ends here, last inning surmised from box.
Wilson with a great running catch
Critz's drive lodges in the space between the flag pole and the fence. Critz circled the bases while Williams and Harper vainly shook the flag pole.
Into the bleachers in left field.
Accounts ends - rest is surmised from box.
Duncan made an error and this is a good place for it.

Friberg and others argued to Ump Klem it was foul

$Mokan made no attempt to run to 1B

Steals were made '...while the pitcher was wondering what he would pitch next.'  Friberg beat the throw home.  The ball briefly got away from Wilson; he snatched it and made a frantic throw to catch Heathcote who had rounded 3B.
If box scores are correct, could be CS(24)
It was Charlie Hargreaves Day at the park

After Terry walked, the game was delayed while friends of Hack Wilson presented him with a gift at the plate.  At this moment rain began to fall and the game was further delayed when bleacherites rushed across the field to seek the shelter of the grandstand.
Rain was falling heavily at this time and the substitution was an obvious attempt by Mgr Fletcher to delay the game.
With 2 strikes on McQuillan Ump McCormick called time due to rain and the game was delayed 15 minutes.
